2.1 Physical Specifications

Parameter Specification Notes
Class Heavy Industrial Quadruped Bipedal configuration available for specialized tasks
Height (Operational) 2.8 meters Adjustable leg extension ±0.5m
Width 1.8 meters Legs extended, reducible to 1.2m for transport
Length 2.4 meters Nose to tail (stowed: 1.8m)
Dry Mass 850 kg Without tools or payload
Maximum Payload 400 kg 38% Earth gravity equivalent
Power System Mass 180 kg Batteries, management, distribution
Structural Mass 420 kg Frame, actuators, joints
Electronics Mass 120 kg Compute, sensors, wiring
Miscellaneous Mass 130 kg Thermal, shielding, interfaces

2.2 Core Functional Capabilities

1. Autonomous Mobility: Traverse 45° slopes, step over 1.5m obstacles
2. Precision Manipulation: ±1mm positioning accuracy for industrial tasks
3. Load Handling: 400kg continuous, 600kg peak (short duration)
4. Tool Operation: Quick-swap between 12+ specialized end-effectors
5. Environmental Interaction: Work in full dust storms, -100°C temperatures
6. Self-Maintenance: Autonomous diagnostics and buddy-system repairs
7. Production Support: Direct integration with smelting and fabrication systems

