3. DETAILED TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE

3.1 Structural System

Frame and Chassis

· Primary Material: Ti-6Al-4V (Grade 5) titanium alloy
· Secondary Material: Carbon fiber reinforced polymer (CFRP) composite panels
· Construction: Hybrid monocoque-space frame with modular attachment points
· Factor of Safety: 1.5 for operational loads, 2.0 for survival loads
· Natural Frequency: >15 Hz to avoid walking gait resonance
· Corrosion Protection: Anodized titanium, ceramic coating on CFRP

Leg Architecture (Quadruped Configuration)

```
Each Leg (4 total):
├── Hip Joint (3 DOF)
│   ├── Flexion/Extension: ±120° @ 90 Nm continuous
│   ├── Abduction/Adduction: ±45° @ 120 Nm continuous  
│   └── Rotation: ±180° @ 60 Nm continuous
├── Knee Joint (1 DOF)
│   └── Flexion/Extension: 0-150° @ 200 Nm continuous
└── Ankle Joint (2 DOF)
    ├── Pitch: ±60° @ 80 Nm continuous
    └── Roll: ±30° @ 60 Nm continuous
```

Joint Actuator Specifications

Parameter Hip 3-DOF Knee Ankle 2-DOF
Type BLDC + Strain Wave BLDC + Planetary BLDC + Strain Wave
Gear Ratio 100:1 150:1 80:1
Peak Torque 180 Nm 300 Nm 100 Nm
Continuous Torque 120 Nm 200 Nm 70 Nm
Speed 30 RPM 20 RPM 40 RPM
Efficiency 85% 90% 82%
Mass 8.5 kg 12 kg 6 kg
Redundancy Dual encoders, dual windings Single encoder, dual Hall Dual encoders

Foot Design

· Diameter: 300mm (circular adaptive sole)
· Contact Surface: Shape-memory polymer with embedded pressure sensors
· Suspension: 50mm vertical travel, oil-dampened
· Ground Penetration Resistance: <5cm in loose regolith at full load
· Self-Cleaning: Electrostatic dust shedding, mechanical scrapers
· Thermal Isolation: Aerogel layer between sole and structure

3.2 Power and Energy System

Primary Energy Storage

· Technology: Solid-state lithium-sulfur (Li-S) batteries
· Nominal Voltage: 400V DC
· Total Capacity: 120 kWh (300 Ah @ 400V)
· Specific Energy: 500 Wh/kg (system level)
· Cycle Life: 2,000 cycles to 80% capacity
· Operating Temperature: -100°C to +60°C (with active thermal management)
· Charging Rate: 1C continuous (120 kW), 2C peak
· Self-Discharge: <1% per month at 0°C

Power Distribution

```
400V Primary Bus
├── Motor Drives (48V via DC-DC)
├── Compute Stack (12V, 48V isolated)
├── Tool Interface (400V direct, 48V logic)
├── Thermal Systems (28V)
└── Communications (12V)
```

Energy Recovery Systems

· Regenerative Braking: 85% efficient in joints during descent/load lowering
· Thermal Harvesting: Thermoelectric generators on motor housings (5% waste heat recovery)
· Solar Supplement: 2m² deployable panels (400W peak during daylight)

Charging Interface

· Connection Type: Inductive coupling (200mm gap)
· Power Transfer: 100 kW maximum
· Alignment: Automated via magnetic guidance (±10mm tolerance)
· Data Transfer: Simultaneous telemetry during charge
· Dust Protection: Active air curtain during docking

3.3 Computational Architecture

Processing Stack

```
Layer 1: Reflexive Control (1ms loop)
├── Processor: 4× ARM Cortex-R52 (lockstep)
├── OS: Bare-metal RTOS
└── Functions: Balance, joint control, emergency stop

Layer 2: Tactical Control (100ms loop)  
├── Processor: 2× NVIDIA Jetson Orin AGX
├── OS: Linux with ROS 2
└── Functions: Path planning, tool control, local mapping

Layer 3: Strategic Planning (10s+ loop)
├── Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8cx Gen 3 (radiation hardened)
├── OS: QNX Neutrino RTOS
└── Functions: Mission planning, resource allocation, learning
```

Sensor Suite

Sensor Type Model/Spec Quantity Function
LIDAR 64-layer rotating, 200m range 2 3D mapping, obstacle detection
Stereo Camera 12MP, RGB-D, 50m range 4 Visual odometry, tool alignment
IMU 9-axis tactical grade 3 Balance, orientation (triple redundant)
Force/Torque 6-axis load cells 8 Ground contact, manipulation force
Current/Voltage 0.1% accuracy Hall effect 48 Power system monitoring
Temperature PT1000 RTD, -200°C to +300°C 36 Thermal management
Radiation Silicon PIN diode spectrometer 2 Dose rate monitoring
Microphone Ultrasonic (20kHz-100kHz) 4 Structural health monitoring

Communication Systems

· Primary: 100 Mbps Ethernet mesh network (rover-to-rover)
· Base Link: 1 Gbps optical fiber when docked
· Long Range: UHF radio, 100 kbps up to 10km
· Earth Link: X-band, 1 Mbps via orbital relay
· Emergency: S-band beacon with 48-hour battery

3.4 Autonomy and Intelligence

Hierarchical Control Architecture

```
LEVEL 1: REFLEXIVE (1ms-10ms)
├── Input: IMU, joint encoders, foot pressure
├── Processing: PD controllers with feedforward
├── Output: Motor torque commands
└── Example: Prevent tip-over when foot slips

LEVEL 2: TACTICAL (100ms-1s)
├── Input: LIDAR, cameras, current task
├── Processing: Model predictive control
├── Output: Gait parameters, tool commands  
└── Example: Navigate around newly detected obstacle

LEVEL 3: STRATEGIC (1min-1hr)
├── Input: Mission objectives, resource state
├── Processing: Constraint optimization
├── Output: Activity schedule, priority decisions
└── Example: Choose between mining and repair tasks
```

AI/ML Capabilities

· Perception: Semantic segmentation of terrain and objects
· Planning: Monte Carlo Tree Search for complex task sequences
· Learning: Federated learning across rover fleet
· Adaptation: Online parameter tuning for changing conditions
· Prediction: Digital twin-based failure forecasting

Autonomous Tool Management

· Tool Recognition: RFID + computer vision verification
· Wear Monitoring: Vibration analysis, current signatures
· Swap Decision: Cost-benefit analysis of tool change vs. continued use
· Calibration: Automatic after each tool engagement

3.5 Quick-Swap Interface (QSI-1)

Mechanical Interface

· Coupling Force: 5,000N clamping (electromechanical wedge)
· Repeatability: ±0.1mm positional, ±0.05° angular
· Connection Time: <30 seconds from approach to locked
· Disconnect Time: <10 seconds (emergency release <2s)
· Dust Sealing: Triple lip seal + positive pressure purge

Utility Connections

```
Power:
├── Primary: 400V DC @ 50A (20kW) - Gold-plated contacts
├── Secondary: 48V DC @ 20A (1kW) - Tool logic power
└── Backup: 12V DC @ 5A - Keep-alive during swap

Data:
├── Optical: 10 Gbps duplex - Primary data channel
├── Electrical: 1 Gbps Ethernet - Backup channel
└── Wireless: 802.11ac (5GHz) - Pre-alignment communication

Fluid:
├── Coolant: Perfluoropolyether - 2L/min @ 200kPa
└── Purge: CO₂/N₂ - 10L/min for dust clearing
```

Tool Head Specifications

Tool Mass Power Function Special Features
RH-2 Harvester 85 kg 8 kW Regolith mining Vibration feedback, ore grading
GR-4 Gripper 45 kg 2 kW Heavy manipulation 4-finger, 500N grip force
LA-3 Laser 65 kg 12 kW Additive manufacturing 2kW fiber laser, powder feed
