3.6 Environmental Protection Systems

Thermal Management

· Passive: 15-layer MLI blankets, low-emissivity surface coatings
· Active: Heat pumps, fluid loops, Peltier elements
· Heat Sources: Motor waste heat, battery discharge heat, RHU units
· Temperature Ranges:
  · Electronics: -40°C to +85°C (operational)
  · Batteries: -20°C to +45°C (optimal)
  · Exterior: -125°C to +125°C (survival)

Dust Mitigation

· Seals: Magnetic fluid seals on rotating joints
· Purge System: Positive pressure N₂ in electronics bays
· Cleaning: Electrostatic dust removal, vibration shaking
· Filtration: HEPA-equivalent on all air intakes

Radiation Protection

· Total Ionizing Dose: 100 krad(Si) capability
· Shielding: 5mm tungsten alloy around critical electronics
· Mitigation: Error-correcting memory, triple modular redundancy
· Monitoring: Real-time dose measurement with automatic safe mode

3.7 Safety and Reliability

Redundancy Architecture

· Critical Systems: Dual or triple redundancy
· Degraded Modes: Operation possible with multiple failures
· Failure Detection: Continuous built-in self-test
· Isolation: Fault containment to prevent cascade failures

Emergency Systems

· Independent Brakes: Spring-applied, electrically released on each joint
· Safe States: Multiple defined safe configurations
· Recovery Modes: Autonomous return to base under fault conditions
· Beacon: Independent power, 30-day transmission capability

Reliability Metrics

· Design Life: 10 Earth years (5 Mars years)
· Mean Time Between Failures (MTBF): 5,000 hours
· Availability: >95% (including scheduled maintenance)
· Fault Coverage: >90% of possible faults detectable

