4. INDUSTRIAL OPERATIONS CAPABILITIES

4.1 Siderurgical Production Chain

Regolith to Metal Process

```
1. EXTRACTION (RH-2 Tool)
   Input: Martian regolith
   Rate: 250 kg/hour
   Efficiency: 85% material recovery

2. BENEFICIATION (Onboard processing)
   Method: Magnetic separation
   Output: 35% Fe concentrate
   Mass Reduction: 65% (waste discarded at site)

3. SMELTING (IC-1 Tool or Foundry Core)
   Process: Carbothermic reduction
   Temperature: 1,500°C
   Yield: 90% of Fe in concentrate
   Output: 15 kg/hour of 95% pure iron

4. REFINING (Foundry Core)
   Process: Basic oxygen or electric arc
   Output: Steel alloys (C, Ni, Cr added from local sources)
```

Production Metrics

Metric Per Sol Per 90 Sols Per Mars Year
Regolith Processed 2,000 kg 180,000 kg 360,000 kg
Iron Produced 120 kg 10,800 kg 21,600 kg
Steel Output 100 kg 9,000 kg 18,000 kg
Energy Consumed 15 kWh 1,350 kWh 2,700 kWh
Mass Efficiency 13.3 kg/kWh 1,200 kg/kWh 2,400 kg/kWh

4.2 Construction and Assembly

Capabilities

· 3D Printing: Metal additive manufacturing at 2.5 kg/hour
· Welding: Structural seams at 0.5 meters/minute
· Assembly: Bolt placement and tightening to 50 Nm torque
· Alignment: ±2mm over 10 meter structures
· Inspection: Non-destructive testing via ultrasonic and thermal imaging

Typical Projects

· Pressurized Module: 4m diameter × 6m length in 30 sols
· Solar Array Foundation: 100m² mounting structure in 10 sols
· Radiation Shelter: 3m thick regolith berm, 20m length in 15 sols
· Roadway: Compacted regolith, 50m × 4m in 5 sols

4.3 Maintenance and Repair Operations

Self-Maintenance

· Lubrication: Automated grease injection to 32 points
· Filter Replacement: Dust filters changed every 500 hours
· Calibration: Weekly sensor and actuator calibration
· Software Updates: Over-the-air during charging

Buddy-System Repairs

```
Protocol: MEDEVAC (Medical Evacuation Analog)
1. Casualty assessment (self-diagnosis + remote scan)
2. Stabilization (immobilize damaged component)
3. Extraction (move to repair facility if possible)
4. Repair (component replacement by buddy rover)
5. Rehabilitation (system test and calibration)
```

