First-Month Performance Projection

By Sol 30, the Vulcan-1 mission will have achieved:

1. Infrastructure Established:
   · Operational base with power, computing, and manufacturing
   · 500m² of mapped and prepared work area
   · Initial storage for 2,000kg of materials
2. Production Demonstrated:
   · 1,200kg of raw regolith processed
   · 120kg of refined Martian steel produced
   · 15m³ of enclosed structure fabricated
3. Autonomy Validated:
   · 95% of operations conducted without Earth intervention
   · Successful tool swaps and minor repairs
   · Adaptation to actual Martian conditions (vs. simulation)
4. Foundation for Scaling:
   · Production rate increasing weekly
   · Learning algorithms optimizing operations
   · Beginning of closed-loop material cycle

