Transition to Sustained Operations (Sol 31+)

The success criteria for the first 30 sols is not raw output, but demonstrated viability of the autonomous industrial model. With the foundation established, operations will scale:

· Sol 31-60: Double production rate, begin construction of Habitat Module #1
· Sol 61-90: Initiate fabrication of AWR-05 (first Mars-built rover)
· Sol 91-120: Expand mining to secondary site 2km distant

This timeline represents the critical bootstrap phase where the AWR-Mars transforms from cargo in a lander to the beating heart of the first Martian industrial base.

